laboratory_examinations.findings: In the dome of the liver, a small 4 mm hypodensity likely representing a small cyst or biliary hamartoma. Six mm hypodensities in the lower pole of the right kidney and in the mid pole of the left kidney likely representing cysts. The tip of the appendix is dilated up to 9 mm with significant surrounding stranding, suggesting either a microperforation or impending perforation. Severe widespread diverticulosis noted.
